TextEng: Made a showing for yourself downstairs, eh? Never make Champion. Not a chance. No way.
Text: 아래서 한건했다고? 용사는 절대 못 돼. 기회 없어. 안 돼.

TextEng: I knew it! I knew you could do it! Gots yourself a Champion Medal! Ask around and they'll tell you I knew you could do it!
Text: 알았다고! 네가 해낼 줄 알았어! 용사의 메달을 땄잖아! 주변에 물어봐, 내가 네가 해낼 줄 알았다고 할 거야!

TextEng: Get on with you. I got no reason to talk with you.
Text: 저리 가. 너랑 얘기할 이유 없어.

TextEng: Stand away from me, you, before I call the tavern guards!
Text: 저리 비켜, 주점 경비원 부르기 전에!

TextEng: More plague-waifs cluttering up the place, I see. Excuse me.
Text: 역병 거지들이 또 몰려들었군. 실례.

TextEng: Go on, you're fouling my air.
Text: 저리 가, 공기 더럽히고 있잖아.

TextEng: If it weren't for this place, I wouldn't go out at all. Plague has closed all my old haunts.
Text: 여기가 아니었으면 아예 안 나왔을 거야. 역병 때문에 단골집이 다 문을 닫았거든.

TextEng: The quarantine has really hurt trade. I wonder how long this place will stay open.
Text: 격리 조치가 무역에 타격을 줬어. 여기가 얼마나 더 영업할 수 있을지 모르겠군.

TextEng: I don't mind being sealed in the Blacklake. I hardly go to the rest of the city, anyway.
Text: 검은호수에 갇혀도 상관없어. 어차피 도시 다른 곳엔 거의 안 가거든.

TextEng: The place is a bit rough, but until the barricades are down, this is the best place for us to gather.
Text: 여긴 좀 거칠지만, 방어벽이 해제될 때까지는 우리가 모일 수 있는 최고의 장소야.

TextEng: You seen pretty friendly for this type of place.
Text: 이런 곳치고는 꽤 친절해 보이는군.

TextEng: Careful around here. You won't want to ruin that pretty face of yours.
Text: 여기서 조심해. 그 예쁜 얼굴 망치기 싫을 테니.

TextEng: Been a while since we had a fresh barbarian face around here. You'll spice things up, I bet.
Text: 새 야만인 얼굴 본 지 오래됐네. 분위기 좀 띄워주겠군.

TextEng: You'll like this place, I'll wager. You look a little rough around the edges.
Text: 여기 마음에 들 거야. 좀 거칠어 보이거든.

TextEng: Oh, I'll enjoy watching you battle in the pit. You look ready for rough-and-tumble.
Text: 오, 투기장에서 싸우는 거 구경하면 재밌겠군. 난투 준비가 된 것 같아.

TextEng: Not much of interest for you around here, magic user.
Text: 여기엔 마법 사용자한테 흥미로운 거 별로 없어.

TextEng: I doubt you'll find this place to your liking, caster.
Text: 여기가 마음에 들 것 같진 않은데, 시전자.

TextEng: A spellslinger? This isn't really your type of place, is it?
Text: 주문쟁이? 여긴 네 스타일 아니지, 그렇지?

TextEng: I take it you are the new owner. Luck be with you in these hard times.
Text: 새 주인인 모양이군. 이 어려운 시기에 행운을 빌어.

TextEng: I am not interested in battling you. Put your weapon away until you need to use it.
Text: 너랑 싸울 생각 없어. 쓸 일 있을 때까지 무기 치워.

TextEng: Yes, yes, I see your fine weapon. Now get it out of my face.
Text: 그래, 그래, 좋은 무기 보여. 이제 내 눈앞에서 치워.

TextEng: Weapons should not be brandished on the main floor. You'll bring unwanted attention.
Text: 메인 플로어에서 무기를 휘둘러서는 안 돼. 원치 않는 관심을 끌 거야.

TextEng: Wherever you fought, it must have been an impressive battle. You are a mess!
Text: 어디서 싸웠든 대단한 전투였나 봐. 완전 엉망이잖아!

TextEng: Look at you. You are in no shape to fight. You need rest.
Text: 꼴 좀 봐. 싸울 상태가 아니야. 쉬어야 해.

TextEng: You look horrible! Isn't the healer doing her job?
Text: 끔찍해 보여! 치료사가 일을 안 하는 거야?

TextEng: Present yourself properly, <man/woman>! Dress yourself!
Text: 제대로 차려입어, <man/woman>! 옷 입어!

TextEng: Kindly cover yourself. You'll bring unwanted attention to the tavern.
Text: 옷 좀 입어. 주점에 원치 않는 관심을 끌 거야.

TextEng: This is hardly the place to risk such behavior. Dress yourself - if not for decency, then at least for battle.
Text: 그런 행동을 할 곳이 아니야. 옷 입어 - 예의를 위해서가 아니라면, 최소한 전투를 위해서라도.
